The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, May 31, 2004  Business Briefs																								 New Delhi, May 30: Overruling the contention of the department of industrial policy and promotion, the Foreign Investment Promotion Board is believed to have waived the 26 per cent divestment condition for TotalFinaElf of France and ExxonMobil Lubricants of the US.																								 Mumbai, May 30: A Reserve Bank (RBI) panel has recommended closure of state finance corporations. In another move, the RBI has extended the off-site surveillance system to non-scheduled urban co-operative banks with deposits of Rs 100 crore and above.																								 New Delhi, May 30: Telecom regulator Trai will issue a consultation paper on spectrum allocation and its pricing on Monday.
